{
  "stem": "4189.1",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So what they did, he came-- this relative, his name was Emmanuel.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "He came to the Belgian border, and he met the train on the Belgium side.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "We were on the train.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And he said to us, when the border patrol comes, you don't say nothing, let me do all the talking.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "So they ask him for his papers, and he, of course, had a French passport.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "He showed his papers.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And they ask him, who are the two children?",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "So he said, those are my children.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "So they didn't bother us, and we went into France.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "So now we were near Paris in Brunoy, he had a little house in Brunoy, that's near Paris.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "Now my mother, again, she was still in Berlin now.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "In the meantime, the uncle from Brussels, from Belgium, from Antwerp, his ship came in and he had to leave for New York.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And my mother was still stuck in Berlin.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And she could not-- there was no way for her to get out.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "As a matter of fact, she got a paper in January of 1939-- she got a paper from the police precinct from Berlin to tell her that she had to leave the territory of the Reich within eight weeks, and if she doesn't leave then she will be subject to imprisonment and heavy fines.",
      "word_count": 54
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And they said that this order can be repealed, but it also said that in the public interest, this appeal will be denied.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So it's a catch-22.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And of course she was desperate and she found some-- through a relative, she found out that in England you could go to England if you would work as a domestic in a household.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Because in England, there was a shortage of domestic help.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
